          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two stacks containing, respectively,16 and 11",
                "enriched 116Cd targets(97.4% 116Cd, 1.5% 114Cd, rest",
                "other stable Cd isotopes) were irradiated in the",
                "external 37 and 16 MeV proton beams att he VUB",
                "cyclotron. The targets were prepared by",
                "electrodeposition on thin Cu strips (Goodfellow,",
                "thickness 12.3 microns) from analkaline bath containing",
                "1g enriched 116Cd. Electro deposition is done by",
                "means of controlled cathode potential electrolysis",
                "at 1.75 V versus amercury/ mercuroussulphate",
                "reference electrode.",
                "Irradiations took place in a Faraday-cup like target",
                "holder. The beam current was kept constant at",
                "approximately 150 nA during the 1500 s irradiation runs",
                "Decay characteristics for the studied  isotopes were",
                "taken from NUDAT2 except for 114mIn where the data from",
                "Browne and Firestone(1986) are used.",
                "For energy degradation in the stack foils a code based",
                "on polynomial approximations for the stopping powers",
                "of the elements present was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
